### API - Test Requests
# This collection contains simple HTTP requests to exercise the local API
# - Use the `/sessions` endpoints to get a JWT for the manager or student user
# - Add the returned token to requests that require authorization as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`
# - The manager user is seeded as: `manager@email.com` / `123456`

### Create a course (requires manager)
POST http://localhost:3333/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: token
{
  "title": "Curso de JavaScript"
}

### List courses (public)
GET http://localhost:3333/courses

### Search courses (public)
GET http://localhost:3333/courses?search=javascript

### List courses ordered by title (public)
GET http://localhost:3333/courses?orderBy=title

### Paginated list (public)
GET http://localhost:3333/courses?orderBy=title&page=1

### Get course by id (logged in)
GET http://localhost:3333/courses/117d7544-12a9-416f-bece-c04db835fd33
Authorization: token

### Update a course (requires manager)
PUT http://localhost:3333/courses/8f37e0b7-4d82-41c3-9f98-0bfbb3354c54
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: token

{
  "title": "Curso de TS"
}

### Delete a course (requires manager)
DELETE http://localhost:3333/courses/8f37e0b7-4d82-41c3-9f98-0bfbb3354c54
Authorization: token

### Login student
POST http://localhost:3333/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "Gabriel25@yahoo.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Login manager
POST http://localhost:3333/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@email.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Example: get a course with token
GET http://localhost:3333/courses/8f37e0b7-4d82-41c3-9f98-0bfbb3354c54
Authorization: token


